<plot>An examination of the life and works of Feng Guodong. An avant-guard artist of China's 70's underground art movement, his short life embodied the haplessness and perseverance of his era. This is a rare view into Beijing's early burgeoning art community, and one of the artists that defined it.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?567577</url></doc>
